abstract: The European Union will extend indefinitely the time limit to resolve disputes in the Iran 2015 nuclear accord to avoid having to go to the U.N. Security Council or triggering new sanctions, the EU's top diplomat said during a visit to Tehran.
snippet: The European Union will extend indefinitely the time limit to resolve disputes in the Iran 2015 nuclear accord to avoid having to go to the U.N. Security Council or triggering new sanctions, the EU's top diplomat said during a visit to Tehran.
lead_paragraph: BRUSSELS — The European Union will extend indefinitely the time limit to resolve disputes in the Iran 2015 nuclear accord to avoid having to go to the U.N. Security Council or triggering new sanctions, the EU's top diplomat said during a visit to Tehran.
headline_main: Europe to Avoid Taking Iran Nuclear Dispute to U.N., EU's Top Diplomat Says
headline_print_headline: Europe to Avoid Taking Iran Nuclear Dispute to U.N., EU's Top Diplomat Says

abstract: The president emphasized a “blue collar” boom in his speech to Congress. But workers in those industries have seen a slowdown — or even losses — in jobs.
snippet: The president emphasized a “blue collar” boom in his speech to Congress. But workers in those industries have seen a slowdown — or even losses — in jobs.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump used his State of the Union address on Tuesday to tick off a laundry list of economic gains, citing record low unemployment for women, higher incomes for households and a “blue collar” boom that he said is underway across America.

abstract: Iran will launch a satellite into orbit by the end of this week, a government minister said on Monday, as part of a fledging program that the United States says is a cover for ballistic missile development.
snippet: Iran will launch a satellite into orbit by the end of this week, a government minister said on Monday, as part of a fledging program that the United States says is a cover for ballistic missile development.
lead_paragraph: DUBAI — Iran will launch a satellite into orbit by the end of this week, a government minister said on Monday, as part of a fledging program that the United States says is a cover for ballistic missile development.
headline_main: Iran to Launch Satellite in Program That U.S. Links to Missiles
headline_print_headline: Iran to Launch Satellite in Program That U.S. Links to Missiles

abstract: President Donald Trump's senior adviser, Jared Kushner, will brief U.N. Security Council ambassadors on Thursday about the Middle East peace plan that Trump unveiled last week, a U.S. official said on Monday.
snippet: President Donald Trump's senior adviser, Jared Kushner, will brief U.N. Security Council ambassadors on Thursday about the Middle East peace plan that Trump unveiled last week, a U.S. official said on Monday.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Donald Trump's senior adviser, Jared Kushner, will brief U.N. Security Council ambassadors on Thursday about the Middle East peace plan that Trump unveiled last week, a U.S. official said on Monday.
headline_main: Trump Adviser Kushner to Brief U.N. Leaders on Mideast Plan
headline_print_headline: Trump Adviser Kushner to Brief U.N. Leaders on Mideast Plan

abstract: The White House excluded CNN on Tuesday from its annual off-the-record briefing with television news personalities prior to the State of the Union address with no public protest from the network or any other journalists who attended.
snippet: The White House excluded CNN on Tuesday from its annual off-the-record briefing with television news personalities prior to the State of the Union address with no public protest from the network or any other journalists who attended.
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — The White House excluded CNN on Tuesday from its annual off-the-record briefing with television news personalities prior to the State of the Union address with no public protest from the network or any other journalists who attended.
headline_main: White House Excludes CNN From Trump Session, With No Protest
headline_print_headline: White House Excludes CNN From Trump Session, With No Protest

abstract: One night each year, the Capitol is transformed for the State of the Union. This year, it happens to be the day before President Trump’s likely acquittal.
snippet: One night each year, the Capitol is transformed for the State of the Union. This year, it happens to be the day before President Trump’s likely acquittal.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — In the uncertain turmoil of American politics, there is reassurance in the predictable pomp of the State of the Union.

abstract: Standing before a Congress and a nation sharply divided by impeachment, President Donald Trump used his State of the Union address to extol a “Great American Comeback” on his watch, just three years after he took office decrying a land of “American carnage” under his predecessor.

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Standing before a Congress and a nation sharply divided by impeachment, President Donald Trump used his State of the Union address to extol a “Great American Comeback” on his watch, just three years after he took office decrying a land of “American carnage” under his predecessor.
